Worker Node IAM Role (EKSNodeRole)

1. AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy
   - Allows the EC2 worker node to communicate with the EKS control plane.
   - Enables the node to join and register with the cluster.

2. AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryPullOnly
   - Allows the worker node to pull container images from Amazon ECR.

3. AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy
   - Allows the Amazon VPC CNI plugin to create and manage ENIs and IP addresses for pods.

Attach this IAM Role to the EKS Managed Node Group.

This is sufficient for:
✔ Joining the EKS cluster
✔ Pulling images from Amazon ECR
✔ Providing networking for pods
